                    "value": "<p>A creature can still eat and drink while sickened by this curse</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[will|dc:18]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> carrier with no ill effects (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @Damage[2d6[void]] damage and the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} until it consumes raw meat (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> as stage 2</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> as stage 2 unless the target has consumed raw meat in the past 24 hours; then it takes @Damage[4d6[void]] damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} until it consumes raw meat</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> If the creature has eaten raw meat in the past 24 hours, it dies and rises as a ghoul; if not, it returns to stage 4 .</p>"
